I have a lot of problems thinking about &quot;how to prevent another Vietnam War&quot; because I do not understand yet how we really got into that mess to begin with. It certainly wasn't a national manifest destiny, or just the stupid acts or decisions of a few self-serving politicians and would-be warriors. It also does not appear to be a singular act or event that caused it. I think I am beginning to look at as a millipede, a moving thing with thousands of tiny legs pushing it along.<br><br>
The best I can do now is to say that I think the best way to prevent another Vietnam War is to develop a national consciousness that will cause us to stumble long before we fall into the pungi pit.
